items.name: Potato
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 12 hours.
items.longDescription:
The potato is a starchy tuber of the plant Solanum tuberosum and is a root vegetable native to the Americas.

**Grow Time:** `12 hours`

items.name: Lettuce
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 15 hours.
items.longDescription:
Lettuce is an annual plant of the daisy family, Asteraceae. It is most often grown as a leaf vegetable, but sometimes for its stem and seeds.

**Grow Time:** `15 hours`

items.name: Carrot
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 18 hours.
items.longDescription:
The carrot is a root vegetable, typically orange in color, though purple, black, red, white, and yellow cultivars exist.

**Grow Time:** `18 hours`

items.name: Broccoli
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 1 day.
items.longDescription:
Broccoli is an edible green plant in the cabbage family.

**Grow Time:** `1 day`

items.name: Tomato
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 1 day and 12 hours.
items.longDescription:
The tomato is the edible berry of the plant Solanum lycopersicum, commonly known as a tomato plant.

**Grow Time:** `1 day and 12 hours`

items.name: Strawberry
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 2 days.
items.longDescription:
The garden strawberry is a widely grown hybrid species of the genus Fragaria, collectively known as the strawberries, which are cultivated worldwide for their fruit.

**Grow Time:** `2 days`

items.name: Corn
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 3 days.
items.longDescription:
Corn also known as maize, is a cereal grain first domesticated by indigenous peoples in southern Mexico about 10,000 years ago

**Grow Time:** `3 days`

items.name: Melon
items.shortDescription: A crop that grows in 7 days.
items.longDescription:
A melon is any of various plants of the family Cucurbitaceae with sweet, edible, and fleshy fruit.

**Grow Time:** `7 days`
